org.hswgt.teachingbox.core.rl.network.rbf

Class RBFNetwork

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.hswgt.teachingbox.core.rl.feature.FeatureFunction
      • org.hswgt.teachingbox.core.rl.network.Network
        • org.hswgt.teachingbox.core.rl.network.rbf.RBFNetwork
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable, Iterable<NetworkNode>

    public class RBFNetwork
extends Network
implements Serializable
    A network of radial basis function. The resulting feature vector will at a position x is the value of each Radial Basis Function at this position. For example: 
     feat(0) = rbf(0).getValue(x)
 feat(1) = rbf(1).getValue(x)
 ...
 feat(n) = rbf(n).getValue(x)
    So the length of the feature vector will be the number of Radial Basis Function in the network. Here is an example of a plotted network with 3 RBFs 
       1 ++--------+---------+---------+----------+---------+---------+--------++
     +         +        |+ |      |+ |       |+ |       +         +         +
     |                 +   +     +   +      +   +                           |
     |                +     +   +     +    +     +                          |
 0.8 ++               |      |  |      |   |      |                        ++
     |               +       + +       +  +       +                         |
     |               |       | |        | |       |                         |
     |              |         |         ||         |                        |
 0.6 ++             +         +          +         +                       ++
     |              |         ||        + |         |                       |
     |             +         + +       +  +         +                       |
     |             |         |  |      |   |         |                      |
 0.4 ++           +         +   +     +    +         +                     ++
     |            |         |    |    |     |         |                     |
     |           +         +     +   +      +         +                     |
     |           |         |      |  |       |         |                    |
 0.2 ++         +         +       + +        +         +                   ++
     |         +         +         +          +         +                   |
     |        +         +         + +          +         +                  |
     +      ++ +      ++ +      ++ + ++       + ++      + ++      +         +
   0 ++--------+---------+---------+----------+---------+---------+--------++
    -2        -1         0         1          2         3         4         5
    Example: 
        RBFNetwork net = new RBFNetwork();
    // add new rbf with mu=0 and sigma=2.
    net.add( new RadialBasisFunction(0,2) );
    // add new rbf with mu=5 and sigma=2.
    net.add( new RadialBasisFunction(5,2) );
    // get value a position 1.0
    DoubleMatrix1D feat = net.getFeatures(new DenseDoubleMatrix1D( new double[] {1} ) );
